The paper discusses privacy-preserving techniques in Bitcoin, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cryptography (cs.CY). The paper also touches upon the political and regulatory aspects of Bitcoin, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
